cs.CR, cs.CY, cs.SE, cs.PL, cs.LG 

The paper discusses a specific type of side channel attack (cache timing attack) on a cryptographic system (AES). Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also involves experiments on designing and implementing countermeasures, which could fall under cs.CY (Computers and Society) as it deals with the ethical implications of security vulnerabilities. The paper also involves software implementation, which could fall under cs.SE (Software Engineering) and cs.PL (Programming Languages). Finally, the paper involves statistical analysis, which could fall under cs.LG (Machine Learning).
